main event: A bright, luminous object was observed in Cyprus Gardens, Florida, on August 9, 1961, descending and accelerating before disappearing, then reappearing and descending again.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 2 minutes., The object emitted intense brilliance as it descended., There were reports of similar sightings in the area., The object appeared to have characteristics of an aircraft with an afterburner., The case was deemed insufficient for further evaluation.
witness description: No specific witnesses were described in the report.
